# campaignfinance — Project Rules

`AGENTS.md` (at the repo root) is the single source of truth for standards,
scope, guardrails, and commands. `CLAUDE.md` and `GEMINI.md` resolve to it.
Read `AGENTS.md` before making changes.

## Stack

Python 3.12+ · uv · Polars + pandas · SQLModel/SQLAlchemy · Pydantic v2 ·
Selenium (state-portal scraping) · pytest + Hypothesis · Ruff · PostgreSQL
(prod) / SQLite (dev).

## Project shape

- `app/abcs/` — abstract base classes (state-agnostic processing interfaces)
- `app/core/` — unified cross-state models, field library, loaders
- `app/ingest/` — schema-driven file parsing (`GenericFileReader`)
- `app/states/` — Texas / Oklahoma implementations
- `app/funcs/` — shared utilities
- `scripts/` — loaders, debug, analysis
- `tests/` — integration · `app/tests/` — unit

## Hard rules

- Parameterized SQLModel/SQLAlchemy queries only — never string-interpolated SQL.
- Log via the `Logger` class (`app/logger.py`), never `print()` in `app/`.
- Secrets resolve through the 1Password SDK (`app/op.py`) — never the `op read` CLI.
- New state code inherits the ABC pattern; field mappings register in the unified field library.
- Consult Context7 before writing against Polars / SQLModel / Pydantic APIs.

Commands, full guardrails, and the Definition of Done live in `AGENTS.md`.
